    "body": "### Problem\n\n**Neovim version:**\n`NVIM v0.12.1`\n\n**Steps to reproduce:**\n\n**Expected:** no error\n\n**Actual:**\n```\nDecoration provider \"start\" (ns=nvim.treesitter.highlighter):\nLua: /usr/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/treesitter/languagetree.lua:215: \nattempt to call method 'range' (a nil value)\n```\n\n**Suspected cause:**\nThe markdown parser query uses `(#set! conceal_lines \"\")` on `fenced_code_block_delimiter` nodes. This predicate appears to call `.range()` on a node internally which is nil in 0.12.1.\n\nRelevant query from MDeiml/tree-sitter-markdown:\n```scheme\n(fenced_code_block\n  (fenced_code_block_delimiter) @markup.raw.block\n  (#set! conceal_lines \"\"))\n```\n\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Open any markdown file\n2. Type a fenced code block with triple backticks\n3. Error appears immediately\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nno error\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nnvim v0.12.1\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nI am not sure I don't have vim I only use neovim and I am not sure how to even report this. I am a noob actually so sorry on my part.\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nDistro  » Arch Linux x86_64, Kernel  » 6.19.11-arch1-1\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nghostty\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nnot set\n\n### Installation\n\nPacman",
