            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Thanks. Given it's not happening with `--clean`, it's sounding much like an nvim-treesitter issue.\nI'll close this for now, unless more specific info pointing to Nvim itself appears. \n\n> I have changed my branch to main\n\nThat's a good start. If the error still persists, you may need to delete and re-install your local copy of nvim-treesitter.\n\nI recall a lazy.nvim user on Matrix also having to regenerate their lock/cache file to get the branch switch to work.\nIf you're also using such a plugin manager, you may likewise need to do something similar.\n\n> and reported this issue there as well\n\nAlso, worth noting you reported the issue to [neovim-treesitter/nvim-treesitter](https://github.com/neovim-treesitter/nvim-treesitter), not [nvim-treesitter/nvim-treesitter](https://github.com/nvim-treesitter/nvim-treesitter) (as the latter was archived). These repositories aren't the same. Not sure if this has an effect on the issue.",
