            "body": "> Also, worth noting you reported the issue to [neovim-treesi](https://github.com/neovim-treesitter/nvim-treesitter)\n\nSir, where I should have reported this bug? I got so irritated that I wrote my neovim config from scratch. treesitter reinstalled by lazy on main branch and install tree-sitter-cli from the pacman. Yeah It is working now not that bug but on main branch of nvim-treesitter many commands arent there which were on master like TSInstallInfo at least that is how I understand it from someone reporting the same issue on github. checkhealth nvim-treesitter now does not show the list of language parsers. So yeah, I enjoy neovim experience but something about treesitter always gets in the way.\nThank you for helping me out.\n\nI wonder if I can do what you are doing. LIke become like you an open source contributor? college first year me.",
